            "1.  Imam   Muhammad   Baqir   (a.s.)   narrates   from   his predecessors  that  the  Holy  Prophet  (s.a.w.s.)  said,  “I  will stand near Mizan on the Day of Judgment. If I see a person whose sins are more than his good deeds I will keep the salutations recited on me by him in the pan of good deeds and make it tilt in his favor.”"
